# GoCloud GitHub wrappers — conventions

## Context

GoCloud builds Terraform **wrapper modules** for GitHub organization management (`terraform-github-wrapper-*`). Each wrapper either:
- **Wraps GitHub provider resources** behind a `*_parameters` / `*_defaults` contract with `for_each` or an enable gate, opinionated defaults, and complementary resources, or
- **Develops a custom child module** under `modules/` when the logic needs typed variables, locals, or multi-resource orchestration.

Typical stack order: Organization → Team → Repository (and related concerns).

---

## Repo layout

Root files / dirs (always present):

```
.github/           # dependabot.yml + workflows (pull-request-events, push-events, scheduled)
.gitignore
CHANGELOG.md
LICENSE
versions.tf        # required_version + required_providers (integrations/github)
variables.tf       # metadata + <service>_parameters + <service>_defaults
metadata.tf        # frozen — provides local.common_name, local.common_tags, local.metadata
locals.tf          # only wrapper-level derived values (may be empty locals { })
data_sources.tf    # only data sources referenced from other .tf files (may be empty)
main.tf            # module blocks
outputs.tf         # caller-facing outputs only
README.yml         # source of truth for generated README
examples/complete/ # lab example
modules/           # child module(s)
```

For complex wrappers, split complementary resource groups into `_<concern>.tf` files (e.g. `_webhooks.tf`, `_memberships.tf`) — do not pack everything into `main.tf`.

Child modules live under `modules/terraform-github-<service>/` (or `modules/github/terraform-github-<service>/` when grouping by provider).

Copy `.github/` from an existing `terraform-*-wrapper-*` repo (same Dependabot + shared reusable workflows). Do not invent ad-hoc CI.

---

## Variables — contract

```hcl
/*--- Common ---*/
variable "metadata" { type = any }

/*--- <Service> ---*/
variable "<service>_parameters" {
  type        = any
  description = "<One line: what this map configures.>"
  default     = {}
}

variable "<service>_defaults" {
  type        = any
  description = "Default values merged into each entry of <service>_parameters."
  default     = {}
}
```

- `type = any` **only** for top-level parameter maps (`*_parameters`, `*_defaults`, `metadata`).
- One-line descriptions; no multi-sentence explanations in `variables.tf`.
- No new root-level knobs (owner, token, org name as standalone vars, etc.) — use `metadata` and `*_parameters`. Configure the GitHub provider in the calling stack / example.
- Additional context variables are allowed when the wrapper consumes outputs from another wrapper (e.g. team IDs, org slug).
- Submodule variables stay **typed** (`string`, `bool`, `map(string)`, etc.); `any` only for open shapes (rulesets, nested objects, policy-like maps).

---

## `metadata.tf` — frozen

Never modify `metadata.tf`. It is a platform template that provides `local.common_name`, `local.common_tags`, and `local.metadata`. Copy it from an existing wrapper unchanged; adapt only if the platform template itself changes.

GitHub resources generally do **not** take AWS-style `tags`; keep `metadata.tf` for platform consistency and naming, but do not invent a `tags =` argument on provider resources that do not support it.

---

## Core pattern — `for_each` + `try()` chain

When iterating over a map of resources, `for_each` may be placed directly on `var.<service>_parameters` or on a local that pre-merges defaults:

```hcl
# Option A — direct (no local normalization needed)
module "<service>" {
  source = "./modules/terraform-github-<service>"

  for_each = var.<service>_parameters

  some_field = try(each.value.some_field, var.<service>_defaults.some_field, <hardcoded_default>)
}

# Option B — local normalization (when defaults must be merged before resolving derived values)
locals {
  <service>s = {
    for k, v in var.<service>_parameters :
    k => merge(var.<service>_defaults, v)
  }
}
module "<service>" {
  for_each   = local.<service>s
  some_field = try(each.value.some_field, <hardcoded_default>)
}
```

**`try()` chain always follows:** `try(each.value.field, var.<service>_defaults.field, <hardcoded_default>)`.
Never use `lookup()` or `coalesce(try(…, null), default)`.

When the wrapper manages a **single** toggled resource (not a map of instances), use an enable gate named `enable_<service>` + `count`, and read fields from the parameters map (not `each.value`):

```hcl
locals {
  <service>_enable = try(var.<service>_parameters.enable_<service>, false) ? 1 : 0
}

module "<service>" {
  source = "./modules/terraform-github-<service>"
  count  = local.<service>_enable

  some_field = try(var.<service>_parameters.some_field, var.<service>_defaults.some_field, <hardcoded_default>)
}
```

Examples: `enable`, `enable_identity_center` (AWS). Prefer this over a bare `enable` key.

Some wrappers iterate over a **sub-key** of the parameters map when the service has multiple resource types:
```hcl
for_each = try(var.<service>_parameters.role, {})
```

---

## `locals.tf` — minimal

Keep only what the root must compute once: derived names, feature gates, cross-resource lookups, data expansion. No child-module business logic here. Keep an empty `locals { }` block when there is nothing to derive (file still present).

```hcl
locals {
  # Feature gate (only when the wrapper manages a single toggled resource)
  <service>_enable = try(var.<service>_parameters.enable_<service>, false) ? 1 : 0
}
```

---

## HCL idioms

- `try(…)` for all optional key reads from `any` maps — never `lookup`.
- `&&` does **not** short-circuit — guard nullable operands with a ternary or intermediate local.
- Compatible with both Terraform ≥ 1.10 and OpenTofu — avoid `regexreplace` and other non-portable built-ins.
- Cross-field validation in child modules: `lifecycle { precondition { … } }` or `variable` `validation` blocks.
- Prefer `integrations/github` `>= 6.0` unless a resource requires a newer minor.

---

## Outputs

Export only IDs, names, slugs, URLs, or maps a parent stack or another wrapper will consume.
Use `try(module.child[0].output, null)` when the child uses `count`.
For `for_each` children, prefer a map keyed by the same keys as `*_parameters`.
Skip debug outputs.

---

## Examples (`examples/complete/`)

```
versions.tf
providers.tf      # provider "github" { owner = local.metadata.github_owner }
metadata.tf       # local.metadata with non-secret placeholders (+ common_name)
locals.tf         # may be empty
data_sources.tf   # may be empty
variables.tf      # same parameter variables as the wrapper (metadata commented)
main.tf           # module "wrapper_<service>" { source = "../../" … }
outputs.tf
README.yml
```

- Assignment syntax only: `<service>_parameters = { … }` — never block syntax.
- No real org names, tokens, emails, usernames, or secrets: use placeholders such as `"example-org"`, `"user1-example"`, `"billing@example.com"`, `"123456789012"`.
- Comment non-default overrides with `# Default: <value>`.
- Set `provider "github" { owner = local.metadata.github_owner }` from example metadata — do not hardcode production owners.

---

## Documentation

`README.yml` is the source of truth for the registry / generated README.
Do not maintain a hand-written root `README.md` if the pipeline generates it from YAML.

---

## Anti-patterns

| Avoid | Prefer |
|-------|--------|
| `lookup(map, k, d)` | `try(map.k, d)` |
| `coalesce(try(…, null), d)` | `try(…, d)` |
| Bare `enable` on single-resource wrappers | `enable_<service>` |
| Missing `.github/` workflows | copy from an existing wrapper |
| AWS-style `tags =` on GitHub resources | omit; use topics/labels only when the resource supports them |
| Root-level `owner` / `token` variables | provider config in the caller / example |
| `&&` with nullable operand | ternary or intermediate local |
| `any` for scalar submodule vars | explicit type |
| Unused `data` blocks | delete |
| Block syntax for map variables | `= { }` assignment |
| Long variable `description` | one line |
| Business logic in wrapper locals | move to child module |
| Modifying `metadata.tf` | copy frozen; never edit |
| Real identities in examples | placeholders only |
